Based on the exhibits, witnesses’ testimony, and the record as a whole, presented or available to the
primary inspector, the following findings of facts were determined:
I contacted the Officer-in-Charge, (OIC) at SCI, Captain Jeffery Johnson and was briefed of the incident.
He indicated that Inmate Daniels was and had been since August 26, 2016. He
advised that at approximately 1:57pm, Officer Fernando Aponte
and discovered Inmate Daniels hanging in the bathroom of his cell U2202. activated
 Inmate Daniels was removed from the noose and Captain Johnson
and Colonel Christopher Edelen immediately
 At approximately 2:35pm, departed SCI with Inmate Daniels
 Inverness. pronounced Inmate Daniels deceased at 3:15pm. The
scene was secured and a crime scene log was started.
I responded to SCI and made contact with Warden John DeBell who indicated that Inmate Daniels’ next of
kin was notified. SAS Neal arrived at SCI and she indicated that Sumter County Sheriff’s Office, (SCSO)
Crime Scene Technician would be responding to work the crime scene. SA Tom Mayes and SA Patel
would be responding to SCI. SA’s Alvin Guzman and Abby George would be responding to
Inverness. Medical Examiner’s Investigator, Felicia Pena contacted SCI and spoke
with SAS Neal about the investigation.
SCSO Crime Scene Technician, Christopher Lightcap, and SA’s Mays and Patel arrived at SCI. SAS
Neal, SCSO Lightcap, SA Mayes and SA Patel entered the crime scene and began their investigation.
SCSO Lightcap processed the crime scene by taking photographs, sketching the scene and collecting
the bedsheet as evidence. SAS Neal, SA Mayes and SA Patel searched through Inmate Daniels’ property
and living area. Once they completed with their search and SCSO Lightcap concluded processing the
crime scene, I released the crime scene back to security.
SCSO Lightcap departed the institution, SA’s Mayes and Patel began interviewing all witnesses. I had
 fax a copy of Inmate Daniels’ o the Medical Examiner’s Office. SA
Patel filled out an investigative demand for records and indicated he would be obtaining a subpoena for
On September 27, 2016, I emailed all records requested to SA Patel, to include Inmate Daniels’ phone
conversations from Securus (Inmate Phone System), incident reports, crime scene and
dormitory logs, photographs taken by security, and .
On January 24, 2017, I received FDLE report TM-37-0015 from SA Patel. I reviewed the report and there
were no administrative issues noted. SA Patel indicated he was closing the case because the 5th
Judicial Circuit Medical Examiner’s Office conducted an autopsy on Inmate Daniels and Doctor Wendy
Lavezzi summarized and advised that she did not believe foul play was involved in the death of Inmate
Daniels. Dr Lavezzi ruled the manner of death as suicide
